# Documentation and Planning Structure

**Plans Location**: Document all plans in `@/0-docs/` folder

**Organization**:
- Create subfolder with appropriate descriptive name for each plan
- Break plans into small, focused step files
- Each file represents one implementation step

**File Structure**:
- Files must be enumerated (01-, 02-, 03-, etc.)
- Order files numerically for correct implementation sequence
- Keep each file focused on single step or milestone

**Example Structure**:
```
@/0-docs/
  project-setup/
    01-environment-setup.md
    02-dependencies-install.md
    03-initial-configuration.md
  feature-x/
    01-research-analysis.md
    02-design-specification.md
    03-implementation-plan.md
    04-testing-strategy.md
```
